#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.13:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:0.2"
msgid "2. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "2. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Assājānīyasutta → ājaññasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Assājānīyasutta "
msgstr "13. A Thoroughbred "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.189, sc1
msgctxt "an8.13:1.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhaddo assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with eight factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and considered a factor of kingship. "

msgctxt "an8.13:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi? "
msgstr "What eight? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño bhaddo assājānīyo ubhato sujāto hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a fine royal thoroughbred is well born on both "

msgctxt "an8.13:1.4"
msgid "mātito ca pitito ca. "
msgstr "the mother’s and the father’s sides. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: This is the Uttarapatha.
msgctxt "an8.13:1.5"
msgid "Yassaṃ disāyaṃ aññepi bhaddā assājānīyā jāyanti, tassaṃ disāyaṃ jāto hoti. "
msgstr "He’s bred in the region fine thoroughbreds come from. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:1.6"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panassa bhojanaṃ denti—"
msgstr "Whatever food he’s given, "

msgctxt "an8.13:1.7"
msgid "allaṃ vā sukkhaṃ vā—"
msgstr "fresh or dry, "

msgctxt "an8.13:1.8"
msgid "taṃ sakkaccaṃyeva paribhuñjati avikiranto. "
msgstr "he eats carefully, without making a mess. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:1.9"
msgid "Jegucchī hoti uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā abhinisīdituṃ vā abhinipajjituṃ vā. "
msgstr "He’s disgusted by sitting or lying down in excrement or urine. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:1.10"
msgid "Sorato hoti sukhasaṃvāso, na ca aññe asse ubbejetā. "
msgstr "He’s sweet-natured and pleasant to live with, and he doesn’t upset the other horses. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: kho panassa honti → yāni kho panassa tāni (s1-3)
msgctxt "an8.13:1.11"
msgid "Yāni kho panassa honti sāṭheyyāni kūṭeyyāni jimheyyāni vaṅkeyyāni, tāni yathābhūtaṃ sārathissa āvikattā hoti. "
msgstr "He openly shows his tricks, bluffs, ruses, and feints to his trainer, "

msgctxt "an8.13:1.12"
msgid "Tesamassa sārathi abhinimmadanāya vāyamati. "
msgstr "so the trainer can try to subdue them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:1.13"
msgid "Vāhī kho pana hoti. "
msgstr "He carries his load, determining: "

msgctxt "an8.13:1.14"
msgid "‘Kāmaññe assā vahantu vā mā vā, ahamettha vahissāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādeti. "
msgstr "‘Whether or not the other horses carry their loads, I’ll carry mine.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:1.15"
msgid "Gacchanto kho pana ujumaggeneva gacchati. "
msgstr "He always walks in a straight path. "

msgctxt "an8.13:1.16"
msgid "Thāmavā hoti yāva jīvitamaraṇapariyādānā thāmaṃ upadaṃsetā. "
msgstr "He’s strong, and stays strong even until death. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:1.17"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhaddo assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "A fine royal thoroughbred with these eight factors is worthy of a king. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.190, sc2
msgctxt "an8.13:2.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant with eight factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi? "
msgstr "What eight? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.4"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panassa bhojanaṃ denti—"
msgstr "Whatever food they’re given, "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.5"
msgid "lūkhaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā—"
msgstr "coarse or fine, "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.6"
msgid "taṃ sakkaccaṃyeva paribhuñjati avihaññamāno. "
msgstr "they eat carefully, without annoyance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.7"
msgid "Jegucchī hoti kāyaduccaritena vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena; "
msgstr "They're disgusted with bad conduct by way of body, speech, or mind, "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.8"
msgid "jegucchī hoti anekavihitānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā. "
msgstr "and by attainment of the many kinds of unskillful things. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.9"
msgid "Sorato hoti sukhasaṃvāso, na aññe bhikkhū ubbejetā. "
msgstr "They're sweet-natured and pleasant to live with, and they doesn’t upset the other mendicants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.10"
msgid "Yāni kho panassa honti sāṭheyyāni kūṭeyyāni jimheyyāni vaṅkeyyāni, tāni yathābhūtaṃ āvikattā hoti satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu. "
msgstr "They openly show their tricks, bluffs, ruses, and feints to their sensible spiritual companions, "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.11"
msgid "Tesamassa satthā vā viññū vā sabrahmacārī abhinimmadanāya vāyamati. "
msgstr "so they can try to subdue them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.12"
msgid "Sikkhitā kho pana hoti. "
msgstr "They do their training, determining: "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.13"
msgid "‘Kāmaññe bhikkhū sikkhantu vā mā vā, ahamettha sikkhissāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādeti. "
msgstr "‘Whether or not the other mendicants do their training, I’ll do mine.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.14"
msgid "Gacchanto kho pana ujumaggeneva gacchati; "
msgstr "They always walk in a straight path. "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.15"
msgid "tatrāyaṃ ujumaggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "And here the straight path is "

msgctxt "an8.13:2.16"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.17"
msgid "Āraddhavīriyo viharati: "
msgstr "They’re energetic: "

#. VAR: nhāru → nahāru (bj, s1, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.13:2.18"
msgid "‘kāmaṃ taco ca nhāru ca aṭṭhi ca avasissatu, sarīre upassussatu maṃsalohitaṃ; yaṃ taṃ purisathāmena purisavīriyena purisaparakkamena pattabbaṃ, na taṃ apāpuṇitvā vīriyassa saṇṭhānaṃ bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Gladly, let my skin, sinews, and bones remain! Let the blood and flesh waste away in my body! I will not stop trying until I have achieved what is possible by manly strength, energy, and vigor.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.13:2.19"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these eight factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.13:2.20"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

